h3. +*Summary*+

Adding inactive customer to organization/customer prompted an error message has encoding issue as below.

 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 


h3. +*Expected Results*+
The error message prompted should not consists of the a href portion and it should be displayed as below.
{code}
This customer is inactive. You'll need to activate their account before you can invite them to the Service Desk.
{code}


h3. +*Actual Results*+

The error message is prompted as below at the moment: 
{code}
This customer is inactive. You'll need to <a href="http://localhost:8382/secure/admin/user/ViewUser.jspa?name=testadmin">activate their account</a> before you can invite them to the Service Desk.
{code}

h3. Problem Definition

There is currently no setting in Service Desk that prevents Agents from adding customers to a project by using the "Add Customers" button from the Project page:
 !AddCustomersButton.png|thumbnail!
h3. Suggested Solution

There is a setting in JIRA Admin > Applications > JIRA Service Desk > Configuration that prevents Agents from adding new organizations, so it might be helpful to have a similar setting here as well that prevents agents from adding new customers:
 !OrganizationManagement.png|thumbnail!
h3. Workaround
 # Disable outgoing email from *JIRA Admin > Outgoing email*.
 However, this setting will impact the entire JIRA instance and no more JIRA notifications will be sent; or
 # Hide the button via CSS added to the announcement banner: 
{panel:bgColor=#ffe7e7}
(i) Atlassian Support *cannot guarantee the provision of any support for the steps described below* as customizations are not covered under [Atlassian Support Offerings|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/Support/Atlassian+Support+Offerings]. Please be aware that this material is provided for your information only and that you use it at your own risk.
{panel}
{code:css|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#6A8EB3|bgColor=#F8F8F8}
<style type="text/css">
button.aui-button.js-invite-customers {
    display: none;
}
</style>
{code}

